The paper deals with the complexity of inference in graphical models, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and artificial intelligence. The paper uses combinatorial hypotheses and graph theory to prove that low treewidth is the only structural restriction that can ensure tractability. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
